#SAMorning Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police have arrested a man for allegedly killing a person at the Menlyn Maine shopping centre in Pretoria on Monday. A video on social media shows the alleged shooting taking place in a parking lot. WATCH: Suspects in Cape lawyer's killing still at large It is understood there was an altercation between the victim and the suspect over the purchase of a vehicle. Security guards at the shopping centre say that the two are business partners who were having lunch together. Police spokesperson Brigadier Mathapelo Peters says police are investigating and that the suspect should be in court within 48 hours of the arrest. Watch the video above for more